<h1>About</h1>

<p>
  Hello! I'm Heather. This website is a place where I share things I'm learning
  and exploring.
</p>

<p>
  Language learning has been a major part of my life for many years. My family
  and I lived in Tajikistan for nearly three decades, where I learned Tajik and
  worked closely with the language and culture. Recently I began learning Greek,
  and my <a href="/diary/">Language Learning Diary</a> documents that journey.
</p>

<p>
  I enjoy experimenting with different approaches to language learning and
  thinking about what actually helps people learn and use a language in real
  life. Many of the activities and articles on this site come from that ongoing
  experimentation.
</p>

<p>
  Beyond language learning, I enjoy exploring other interests as well —
  including technology, AI tools, and creative projects like knitting. This site
  is meant to be a small window into those interests and the things I’m
  currently learning.
</p>

<p>
  If you're interested in Tajik language learning, you can also visit my other
  site:
  <a href="https://talktajiktoday.com" target="_blank">Talk Tajik Today</a>.
</p>
